{"_id":"qLXNi9sr82rz60ji","name":"Using Ability Scores","permission":{"default":0,"rLGPG2tW0qo9mHmp":3},"folder":"","flags":{},"content":"<p>Six abilities provide a quick description of every creature&rsquo;s physical and mental characteristics:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Strength</strong>, measuring physical power</li>\n<li><strong>Dexterity</strong>, measuring agility</li>\n<li><strong>Constitution</strong>, measuring endurance</li>\n<li><strong>Intelligence</strong>, measuring reasoning and memory</li>\n<li><strong>Wisdom</strong>, measuring perception and insight&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong> Charisma</strong>, measuring force of personality</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Is a character muscle-bound and insightful? Brilliant and charming? Nimble and hardy? Ability scores define these qualities&mdash;a creature&rsquo;s assets as well as weaknesses.</p>\n<p>The three main rolls of the game&mdash;the ability check, the saving throw, and the attack roll&mdash;rely on the six ability scores. The book&rsquo;s introduction describes the basic rule behind these rolls: roll a d20, add an ability modifier derived from one of the six ability scores, and compare the total to a target number.</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5e.rules.nFdBKy0SAgsIhi7T]{Ability Scores and Modifiers}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5e.rules.Au49u5X1n0R8Ali4]{Advantage and Disadvantage}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5e.rules.PaKUefllxSnLDjaI]{Proficiency Bonus}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5e.rules.kMQcMfFY7VGMkKrP]{Ability Checks}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5e.rules.tK5FwAIu92di2zLZ]{Using Each Ability}</p>\n<p>@Compendium[dnd5e.rules.ekSNjjsCSyl2kxEi]{Saving Throws}</p>"}
